review_blob: A clear, dark amber ale with a off-white creamy head, with little retention.  A pleasant aroma, slightly hoppy.  A semi-sweet, medium bodied taste.

An interesting ale, with a reddish color, tan head with medium rentention.  The taste is chocolatey nut flavour, with little to no hop flavor - a very malt centered taste profile.  Medium bodied with a thin texture.  Best fresh from the fridge.  Certainly a unique flavour with a strong malt profile.
A good session beer, not too heavy, the hops are not over powering, good color and a nice aroma, finishes nicely.
caramel & roasty nose, a clean amber color, minimal head, light body, thin mouth feel, with average carbonation.
